    "summary": "The Board's role, as outlined in Article 66 of the EU AI Act, is to assist and advise the Commission and Member States in applying the regulation effectively and consistently. This includes coordinating with national authorities, sharing expertise and best practices, advising on the enforcement of rules on AI models, and harmonising administrative practices. The Board can also issue recommendations on relevant matters, support the Commission in promoting AI literacy, facilitate the development of common criteria, cooperate with other Union institutions, and assist in developing the necessary expertise for implementing the regulation.",
